55. mallem: this reading is per· haps preferable to malim, inasmuch as hoc seems to indicate that the person supposed has the spring to draw from but not the river; hence the construction might naturally be contrary to fact.

57. si quos delectet, whoever takes pleasure in, etc. The state- mentis a kind of parable continu- ing the case supposed in v. 54.

58. Aufidus: Horace as usual takes a particular river, the one near his birthplace, to represent any. rapid stream.
